A constant template is finished during compilation.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    title #= "Beanstalk"

    heading #= [$md:
        # [title]
    ]
]

A direct top-level const template in an HTML entry can also become part of the
generated page:

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    #[$md:
        # Compile-time heading
    ]
]

Const template loops have an iteration limit so an accidental build-time loop
cannot run forever.
